## 3. Boundaries & Constraints (The "Guardrails")
Functional Boundary:** KapwaRelief is nota Search and Rescue (SAR) dispatch. We refer life-and-death rescue requests to the proper authorities (911/PCG) and focus purely on Relief & Recovery.
Geographic Boundary:** Limited to specific "Active Operations Zones" defined at the start of each disaster event to prevent the map from becoming unreadable.
Data Retention Boundary:** Data is "Live" for 21 days post-disaster. On day 22, it is moved to `reports.KapwaRelief.ph` and stripped of high-res images on the main server to keep the site fast.
Privacy Boundary:** While data is transparent, we adhere to the **Data Privacy Act (DPA)**. Recipient names are anonymized in public reports (e.g., "Family A.R. – Brgy. 1") but kept in the secure back-end for auditing.
Boundary & Method (The "Verified" Workflow)
How we ensure the data is accurate without using heavy official sensors:

Boundary: The dashboard only displays pins within a defined operational radius (e.g., "Typhoon Pepito Response - Bicol Region").

Verification Method:

Submission: Field Lead submits a report via a lightweight text-based form.

Assessment: Admin checks the report (usually via a quick Viber/Telegram call to the Lead).

Activation: Once "Verified," the pin appears on KapwaRelief.ph.

Archiving: Once "Completed," the data is moved to reports.KapwaRelief.ph and deleted from the live map database.
